MODIFIERS.103,7: MESSAGE:If you master Mario Editor's warp system, you can make massive and complex levels for others to play!
MODIFIERS.75,7: MESSAGE:Now this is where things really start to get complicated. Section warping! Place a text modifier, and use a comma to seperate the warp destination from the section.
MODIFIERS.49,8: MESSAGE:Follow this setup for big pipes!
MODIFIERS.31,8: MESSAGE:Now you have set a destination! Now, place a warp marker with a text modifier that matches the destination to warp there!
MODIFIERS.77,7: MESSAGE:Text modifier format:       Destination,Section             Remember this!
MODIFIERS.41,8: MESSAGE:The exact same setup works for doors! Awesome!
MODIFIERS.4,4: MESSAGE:Want to make SUPER COMPLEX levels? Mario Editor's warp system has you covered. Lets go over everything in detail...
MODIFIERS.91,7: MESSAGE:Same thing applies to doors, beanstalks, and warp note blocks. For beanstalks, place a warp marker at the top of the level.
MODIFIERS.28,8: MESSAGE:Now for the fun part. Destination markers. Place them where you would normally place a Mario object. This means top left corner for warp Mario.
MODIFIERS.12,8: MESSAGE:First, pipes! Think of warping Mario as a 2x2 square. Use arrows on the edges of the pipes, just like the following examples!

MODIFIERS.14,18: MESSAGE:Welcome to the Mario Editor Tutorial! For the full experience, make sure that you play AND edit this level!

MODIFIERS.110,5: MESSAGE:You can use text modifiers to make Bowser fire before he is even on screen!
MODIFIERS.27,5: MESSAGE:Some items will change their orientation based on their surroundings, like those ceiling diagonal cannons, for example.
MODIFIERS.7,7: MESSAGE:This part of the tutorial will be used to document various things that did not fit anywhere else.
MODIFIERS.85,5: MESSAGE:Speed modifiers change the speed of touch-start objects, block trains, and the autoscroller. These specific items also react differently to arrow modifiers.
MODIFIERS.145,8: MESSAGE:Almost forgot to mention the classic scroll setting. Use this to prevent the screen from scrolling left.
MODIFIERS.138,6: MESSAGE:The end boss orb will spawn when all boss category enemies are defeated in a section, and will clear the level when collected.
MODIFIERS.71,5: MESSAGE:All enemies in the persistent tab will be active throughout the entire section unless you specify a destination with a text modifier.
MODIFIERS.15,5: MESSAGE:You can use arrow modifiers to change the starting direction for a whole bunch of different things!
MODIFIERS.83,5: MESSAGE:Thanks to markers, those annoying bullets only fire when Mario is in that box over to the left. That space is in between the bullet spawner and the destination marker

MODIFIERS.19,21: MESSAGE:When you have something selected, you will only delete stuff in the same layer. If you have nothing selected, you will delete everything below your cursor.
MODIFIERS.37,21: MESSAGE:Did you see the gold outline on your health meter? That means that you will not lose your powerup when you get hurt! Use this to make levels that require powerups!
MODIFIERS.16,21: MESSAGE:Using Mario Editor is easy! Just select something to place from the top menu, and place it down with left click. Use the right click to delete stuff.
MODIFIERS.104,18: MESSAGE:Use the arrow keys while holding down SHIFT to resize the level. You will not be able to make the level smaller if there are things placed in the way.
MODIFIERS.72,21: MESSAGE:Mario Editor supports infinite checkpoints per level. Make sure to use LOTS of checkpoints in your levels. People will thank you!
MODIFIERS.95,15: MESSAGE:That trap was unfair, right? Thankfully, you didn't have to replay the whole level to get back here thanks to checkpoints! Woohoo!
MODIFIERS.41,21: MESSAGE:Each level is made up of multiple sections. Each section is like its own mini level. Link together multiple sections to create mega levels!
MODIFIERS.26,18: MESSAGE:Normal tiles have collisions associated with them automatically! Background tiles do not. Background tiles also appear behind piranha plants!
MODIFIERS.53,18: MESSAGE:You can test out your levels without saving them! Simply click play to do so!
MODIFIERS.45,21: MESSAGE:The settings in the Settings menu are section specific. Give each section its own unique flair!

MODIFIERS.131,21: MESSAGE:Text modifiers let you modify things with the power of user input! In the editor, you can hover your cursor over placed text modifiers to read their contents.
MODIFIERS.51,16: MESSAGE:Here are some more item modifier examples...
MODIFIERS.7,22: MESSAGE:In Mario Editor, modifiers are used to modify the behavior of other objects you have already placed. Look at these blocks, for example.
MODIFIERS.161,17: MESSAGE:The message modifier lets you write more refined text for your message boxes. Nya~
MODIFIERS.90,22: MESSAGE:Arrow modifers can be used to modify the movement of certain objects. Here are a few examples.
MODIFIERS.32,22: MESSAGE:Wow, Mario Editor has a lot of different powerups. Either way, these blocks have been modified with item modifiers. These are pretty easy to use.

MODIFIERS.14,8: MESSAGE:At the start of a section, warp Mario moves rightwards, so you need to put an arrow directly to his right, like this.

MODIFIERS.26,22: MESSAGE:Make sure to share your levels with the world when you are done with them. I'm sure people would love to download and play them!
MODIFIERS.22,22: MESSAGE:Hello Mario Engine is a clean, organised, fully commented, and user friendly Mario engine that can be used with GameMaker: Studio!
MODIFIERS.40,22: MESSAGE:For maximum performance, Mario Editor has been compiled with the YoYoCompiler! That's right, you are running compiled C++ code!
MODIFIERS.24,22: MESSAGE:If you want to make a full game, or customise the graphics, audio, or code, then you should be using the Hello Mario Engine instead. Mario Editor is all about levels!
MODIFIERS.20,22: MESSAGE:Oh, one more thing! Happy 10th anniversary Hello Mario Engine! Hello Mario Engine is the open source Mario engine that Mario Editor uses!
MODIFIERS.6,22: MESSAGE:This is it for the Mario Editor tutorial! It is now your job to use everything you know to create something amazing! Go for it!
MODIFIERS.42,22: MESSAGE:So make your levels as big as you want! Make them huge! Push Mario Editor to its limit! YAHOO! MAMA MIA!
